{"blocks":[{"key":"dp05l","text":"This protocol describes how to quantify 16S rRNA bacterial gene or transcript copy numbers using Droplet Digital PCR technology (ddPCR) from Bio-Rad. This is an up-to-date modification of a classical bacterial enumeration qPCR-assay. This assay uses the EvaGreen™ chemistry. The primers are taken from Yu et al. (2005).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":97,"length":38},{"key":1,"offset":302,"length":16}],"data":[]},{"key":"bpdm2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"cn28p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"cf0qa","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":2,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"4vcdm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"33ef6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":3,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":[]},{"key":"ea8s7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"A1B58FD074D811EA9D8A11E1CA31FA49","url":"https://www.bio-rad.com/en-cz/applications-technologies/droplet-digital-pcr-ddpcr-technology?ID=MDV31M4VY"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"3881307204BC11EBB7D70A58A9FEAC2A","url":"http://dx.doi.org/10.1002/bit.20347"}},"2":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":[],"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":29,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"1bsub","text":"Advantages of ddPCR over qPCR
Among the biggest advantages of the ddPCR technique are its high sensitivity (down to one molecule of target gene presented in input DNA) and low sensitivity to enzymatic inhibitors. Moreover, because it is an absolute and direct quantification technique, no external standard is needed for evaluation.

